post_text: We have BIG NEWS! We are thrilled to announce that Bannockburn School has been named a National Blue Ribbon School for 2019! Bannockburn’s award falls within the category of “Exemplary High Performing Schools.” This means Bannockburn School is among the state’s highest performing schools! Check out this video to learn what makes Bannockburn so great!

post_text:
The Fuel Up to Play 60 Healthy Eating Bag Tags are back again this year and we plan to encourage healthy foods in lunches from home. We also hope to see backpacks and lunch bags filled with tags again this school year! We met up with Staley Da Bear, Chicago Bears mascot, ahead of the Bears vs. Packers game this weekend and he shared with us his favorite healthy foods...Corn, Peppers, and Cheese Heads!

Any student who brings in Corn, Peppers, or Cheese in their lunch beginning tomorrow 9/6 through next week 9/14, will receive a Healthy Eating Tag from one of our Fuel Up to Play 60 student team members during their lunch period. Who knows, students might be able to get their tag autographed by Staley in person at our kickoff event coming up on October 3rd? More info to come.

Students are using our 3D printer, experimenting with our new Air Parrot Drone, building with Knex and Zometool, playing with a 3D pen, and participating in digital media tools such as iMovie, Final Cut Pro and Garageband.
